"Teams in Organizations" is an intensive, interactive and experiential course focusing on various aspects of the teamwork. Even though it is a theory-based course, it applies highly practical approach to the subject matter. The course is designed to provide students with essential understanding of teamwork fundamentals to become more effective and productive team member.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the basic fundamentals of teamwork, both the central concepts as well as the main processes of teamwork will be covered. Practicums provide students with an opportunity to raise their practical awareness about key factors and skills essential for teamwork in order to become more effective team member.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - understands the essence of teamwork, incl. the main concepts and processes driving effective teamwork; - is more aware of his/ her contribution to the teamwork and analyze the team's effectiveness and performance.
